{"id":14881765,"mediaExerciseId":"12da99fd-3193-4d85-bcb1-7b43be9dc139","exerciseName":"7","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612470,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":735,"solutions":[{"id":5979969,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to give insights regarding multinational corporations.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The exercise mentioned that multinational firms have much greater sales outside their domestic markets. Domestic market sales are important to a business since it is the basis of the company's status within their country.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/3db872de500e76864120ee6a050b596a/ecdf24ab9cf9b93e7b79de41026886c1/lateximg_large.png","width":1062},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/3db872de500e76864120ee6a050b596a/ecdf24ab9cf9b93e7b79de41026886c1/lateximg.png","width":531}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Hence, domestic currency is **still relevant** regardless if the sales outside their domestic market is greater. The sales outside will still be converted into the domestic currency for *financial statement purposes*. The financial statements of the company will only show a single currency which is the domestic currency.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/3db872de500e76864120ee6a050b596a/7a941e5e1a077d086bd29ab0b641b7cb/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/3db872de500e76864120ee6a050b596a/7a941e5e1a077d086bd29ab0b641b7cb/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Moreover, the *financial performance* of the company is computed using domestic currency. To compute earnings per share, current ratio, debt ratio, and other financial ratios, the sales from foreign market must be converted into the domestic currency.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/3db872de500e76864120ee6a050b596a/d58f15f920dfab76b6187f127c97d299/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/03/3db872de500e76864120ee6a050b596a/d58f15f920dfab76b6187f127c97d299/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, domestic currency is still relevant as it will be used in financial statements and to check financial performance of multinational companies.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"c3c62811-f73b-4b3d-9fd4-9d09d74f1938","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881766,"exercis